oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Price daughters on automobile
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Three children sitting on the front of an automobile. (L to R) Mary "Snooky" Clair, Henrietta "Net" Price Baldwin, and Eloise Price Alley (1925-2020). They are daughters of Richard P. Price (1868-1952) and Gwendolyn (Bumbalough) Price (1892-1976). The car belonged to Mrs. Oscar Carta.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Families; Automobiles; Girls; Children
